SIMPLE: hungry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hungry
<hw>Hun"gry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Hungrier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Hungriest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>hungrid</ets>. See
<er>Hunger</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Feeling hunger; having a keen
appetite; feeling uneasiness or distress from want of food; hence,
having an eager desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Showing hunger or a craving desire;
voracious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cruel, <qex>hungry</qex> foam.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cassius has a lean and <qex>hungry</qex> look.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not rich or fertile; poor; barren; starved; <as>as,
a <ex>hungry</ex> soil</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>hungry</xex>
beach.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunk</ent>⟦br⟧
